      Hologram crypto fraud
   =20
 =20

The basic form of cryptocurrency fraud is that you send a venture capitalis=
t a Twitter direct message saying =E2=80=9Chi can you send me the password =
to your NFT wallet=E2=80=9D and he replies =E2=80=9Csure, here you go!=E2=
=80=9D and you take all of his non-fungible tokens. On the other hand I gue=
ss there are  more baroque approaches:
A set of hackers managed to impersonate Binance chief communications office=
r (CCO) Patrick Hillmann in a series of video calls with several representa=
tives of cryptocurrency projects. The attackers used what Hillman described=
 as an AI hologram, a deepfake of his image for this objective, and managed=
 to fool some representatives of these projects, making them think Hillmann=
 was helping them get listed on the exchange.
I=E2=80=99m not sure I even understand why that would be valuable (did holo=
gram Hillmann ask these projects to pay for those fake listings?) but, sure=
, hologram crypto fraud.

