The small, money-losing New Jersey deli that was once the sole asset of a p=
ublicly traded company with a bizarre market capitalization of $100 million=
 has been sold and closed, according to a regulatory filing.
Your Hometown Deli in Paulsboro, New Jersey, had been =E2=80=9Ctemporarily =
closed=E2=80=9D on June 19 while its management sought a new buyer, Makamer=
 Holdings said in a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission.
On July 1, Makamer sold the deli=E2=80=99s remaining inventory for $700. An=
d then on Aug. 9, the company =E2=80=9Cdisposed of its subsidiary Your Home=
