ough authorized shares to fully convert their convertibles. =E2=80=9CHave t=
hem convert into common-equivalent preferred stock, then get shareholder ap=
proval for more shares=E2=80=9D was kind of the go-to advice there, sometim=
es with a penalty interest rate on the preferred (or the convertibles) if y=
ou don=E2=80=99t get the shareholder approval soon enough. This is not a th=
ing that companies do every day, but in the world of arcane equity financin=
