the penny-stock company), and then you trick naive public investors into bu=
ying the stock from you for more money. There are some pretty well-known tr=
aditional=C2=A0methods for tricking the public:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Especially if you control the company=
, you go around issuing press releases about how the company has found a cu=
re for cancer or is pivoting to the blockchain or whatever. Retail investor=
s are fooled and buy the stock.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Ev=
en if you don=E2=80=99t control the company, you put out a fake press relea=
se saying that Tesla Inc. has offered to buy the company, and then dump you=
r stock quickly while the market is fooled.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bott=
om: 5px;">You sell some stock to your friend for $0.02, she sells it back t=
o you for $0.03, you sell it back to her for $0.04, she sells it back to yo=
u for $0.05, you post on some message boards saying =E2=80=9CTHIS STOCK IS =
SOARING, LOOK AT THIS PRICE ACTION,=E2=80=9D and then you sell to the reade=
rs of those message-board posts for $0.06 and split the profits with your f=
riend.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You post on a message board=
 saying =E2=80=9Chey I=E2=80=99m gonna pump this stock=E2=80=9D and other p=
eople say =E2=80=9Csure all right sounds fun.=E2=80=9D <em>They=C2=A0</em>b=
uy the stock=C2=A0as part of a conscious game of musical chairs:=C2=A0<em>S=
omeone=C2=A0</em>will be left holding the bag, overpaying for worthless sto=
ck and unable to sell before it collapses, but everyone has fun playing the=
 game and trying to get out in time.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There might be a few others, and you can combi=
